caption.text:
One of the best moment in 2016 so far: my 21st birthday ‚ò∫Ô∏è and my boyfriend deserves this post with long caption üòÅ
.
.
.
Tbh, gak nyangka Dicky bakal jadi orang paling sweet di dunia di mata aku. Dari awal deket sampe jadian, Dicky terlihat sebagai orang yang cukup cuek. Lama-kelamaan, aku sadar perhatian Dicky lebih dari yang dibayangkan. Dia justru jadi orang nomor satu (selain bunda) yang ngingetin ini itu dan merhatiin aku sedetil itu. Sampai akhirnya kita LDR Jakarta-Tokyo untuk beberapa bulan ke depan, dan dia gak bisa ada di beberapa hari penting aku: IMO dan ulang tahun. Syukurnya, dia selalu kasih never ending support, walau beda 3.956 mil ya jaraknya üòÇ Ternyata, semua perintilan ulang tahun pun udah disiapin sejak beberapa bulan sebelum berangkat ke Jepang. Mulai dari bikin video, nyari dan beli kado, bungkus kado, pesen ini itu, beli dekorasi, dan SEMUA itu harus dititip ke @kristilevania dan teman-teman lain buat disampein ke aku pas hari H ulang tahun (huge thanks to them!). Di hari H ultah (19 Okt) cuma bisa ngerayain via video call jam 00.00 WIB dan paginya di kelas dikasih kue yang super lucu + sambil vid call melalui Vanya. Dari situ, "permainan" mencari 21 kado dimulai, harus ngambil kado ke A, B, C, dst yang lagi kuliah di ruang X atau makan di kantin (karena kebetulan lagi beda modul). Pencarian kado gak cuma sehari gaes, lanjut sampe besoknya dan hari ini (21 Okt). Sampe akhirnya berhasil ngumpulin 19 kado, terus 2 sisanya kemana? Ternyata temen2 baru ngerayain bareng hari ini, bersama balon-balon dekor yang sudah dititip Dicky hampir sebulan lalu üòÇ  Akhirnya, 2 kado terakhir pun dikasih. Alhamdulillah lengkap 21 kado yeay üíï
.
.
.
Dicky, terima kasih ya semua effortnya selama ini untuk buat bahagia. Bukan masalah seberapa banyak jumlah kadonya, seberapa fancy perayaannya, tapi usaha kamu. Terima kasih sudah engage dengan keluarga dan teman-teman aku, dan jadi my wish-come-true-boyfriend. Semoga segala kebaikan yg kamu lakukan untuk aku (dan untuk orang lain) berbuah kebaikan yang jauh lebih besar untuk diri kamu ya üòä Lastly, terima kasih sudah jadi orang yang tulus, I love you üíú

caption.text: Rindu.

Tepat setahun yang lalu (17 Oktober 2015), dua orang ini cuma bisa foto bawa balon. Hari ini (15 Oktober 2016) akhirnya bisa foto bawa medali, alhamdulillah :") Bersama Hiradipta, temen gue yang jenius ini, alhamdulillah kita bisa sama-sama berjuang buat bawa pulang medali IMO untuk FKUI. Setelah harus berpuluh-puluh kali naik gojek PP Salemba-RS Harapan Kita dan Salemba-RS Persahabatan, ikut sympo workshop sana sini, pulang malem karena belajar di perpus, ngejalanin puluhan bimbingan, dan masih banyak pengorbanan lain, akhirnya dapet kesempatan juga ngasih emas untuk FKUI di Indonesian International Medical Olympiad Cabang Kardiorespirasi.

Gue dan Hiradipta punya banyak kesamaan, tapi banyak banget juga perbedaan. Kadang suka ngomong ngegas satu sama lain pas lagi ngejelasin sesuatu (niatnya gak marah, cuma ngegas aja gak tau kenapa wkwk). Herannya, pas lagi belajar bareng suka heboh pertahanin argumen masing-masing dalam jawab soal. Di balik kekurangan itu semua, kita saling ngecover dalam setiap kesulitan saat persiapan sampe hari H kompetisi. I couldn't have made it this far if I weren't with her! Dear Dipta, we have achieved one of our goals in 2016. So, what's next? üòä

Giant Egg Tart aka Pie Susu üç∞ This is my favorite cake to make. The recipe is simple, my family and my boyfriend loved it (I hope he really did üòÖ). Needless to say, the taste was sort of like Pie Susu "Enak" Bali HAHA. So, here is my egg tart recipe ‚ò∫Ô∏è
.
Pastry:
- 250 g plain flour
- 1 egg
- 100 g margarine
- 1 tbsp sugar
- pinch of salt
.
Custard/filling:
- 250 cc sweet condensed milk
- 200 fresh milk
- 4 egg yolk
- 2 tbsp maizena flour
- pinch of salt
.
To make the pastry, mix flour, egg, margarine, sugar and salt well. Once it is well mixed, press the mixture together and form a dough by using hand. Line dough in the middle of tart case, lightly press the dough into the tart case. Refrigerate for about 15 mins while you make the filling.
.
To make the filling, beat egg yolks with milk and sweet condensed milk, add maizena flour and pinch of salt. Mix it well and sift the mixture. Pour the mixture carefully into the tart shell. Bake tart for 40 mins at 180 degree C.

caption.text: Maluv

Do you know the almost-famous Swedish meatballs by IKEA? The taste of tender meatballs with creamy sauce, fluffy mashed potatoes, and lingonberry jam is nice, with a hint of sweetness. So, here is the mouthwatering recipe for your Swedish meatballs.
.
MEATBALLS
- 100 g ground chicken
- 400 g ground beef
- 1 egg
- 2 garlic
- 1/2 stir-fried onion
- 1 tbsp corn starch
- 1/4 cup of bread crumbs
- 60 cc full cream milk
- 1/4 tbsp oregano
- 1/2 tbsp salt
- 1/4 tbsp pepper
.
SAUCE/GRAVY
- 1 tbsp butter
- 1 tbsp white flour
- 1 tbsp tomato sauce
- 1 tbsp oyster sauce
- 200 cc beef broth
- 250 cc full cream milk
- pinch of sugar, salt, and pepper
.
MASHED POTATOES
- 2 medium potatoes
- 1/2 tbsp butter
- 100 cc full cream milk
- pinch of salt and pepper
.
In large bowl, combine ground beef and chicken with other ingredients. The key to make tender meatballs is bread crumbs. Stir until well combined with your clean hands. Roll the mixture onto meatball form. Cook the meatballs completely until all sides are brown with butter in the frying pan.
.
Let's make the sauce or gravy! Melt the butter, add flour, and whisk them well until the thick structure formed. Add tomato sauce and oyster sauce, beef broth, and milk. Season with salt and pepper. Add the meatballs into the sauce and cook for 2 minutes.
.
The basic mashed potato is easy to make. Cook potatoes in boiling water until tender but still firm. Mash with potato masher or ricer. Blend with butter and milk until smooth and creamy, season with salt and pepper.
.
The original Swedish meatballs use lingonberry jam. I hardly can find it, so I don't use this kind of jam :( The Swedish meatballs can be served with vegetable to give more color on your plate üç≤üçõ

caption.text: Oreo cheesecake, anyone? Personally, I like making no-bake cheesecake because it doesn't need oven and eggs (which contains high cholestrol üòÖ). First things first, let's make the crust by mixing melted butter thoroughly with oreo biscuit crumbs. Spread in the jar while pressing it. To firm up the crust, chill it in the freezer for at least 10 mins before adding the filling. Second, to make the filling, add 200 cc whipped heavy cream, 250 g cream cheese, oreo crumbs, 1 tbsp vanilla, 3 tbsp sugar, 1/2 tbsp lemon juice in the bowl then beat them well with electric mixer until the batter become thick. Pour into chilled crust and leave it in the fridge for several hours or overnight. Oh, this is a super easy yet tasty cheesecake.
